The paper deals with gender classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of AdaBoost-based score fusion also suggests a machine learning approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a new face dataset, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories.
